### Step 7: Verification Gate (MANDATORY)

Before ending the phase, verify the updated markdown.

For EACH variant V, verify:

| Gate | Check |
|---|---|
| Scratch exists | `02_updated_tcs_<V>.md` exists and is non-empty. |
| Final exists | Updated deliverable `.md` file(s) exist. |
| Scratch ↔ final consistency | Final content equals scratch, or final multi-part concatenation equals scratch. |
| Approved plan coverage | Every approved `UPDATE`, `ADD`, `RETIRE`, `SPLIT`, `MERGE` action was applied. |
| No unapproved edits | No TC was changed outside the approved report unless required by formatting consistency. |
| TC ID uniqueness | No duplicate active TC IDs. |
| TC ID stability | Existing IDs preserved unless explicitly approved. |
| Totals | Prelude totals match active TC rows. |
| GUI/FUNC split | GUI/FUNC counts match section rows. |
| RTM coverage | 100% of in-scope new audited ACs are covered. |
| Removed behavior | Removed requirements are not still covered by active obsolete TCs. |
| Feedback coverage | User feedback is applied or explicitly recorded as not applied. |
| Heading schema | Prelude uses `#` and `####`; screens use `##`; GUI/FUNC use `###`. |
| Table schema | TC tables remain converter-compatible. |
| Variant correctness | No platform-specific TC is written into the wrong variant. |
| ADD_VARIANT completeness | Every requested new variant has a full `.md`, scratch, prelude, RTM, and TC set using the target variant rubric. |

If verification fails:

1. Recover final `.md` from `02_updated_tcs_<V>.md` if the failure is a partial/mismatched final write.
2. Re-run verification once.
3. If verification still fails, STOP and report the exact failed gate(s). Do NOT trigger `.xlsx` conversion.

